NNAAMMEE
       sge_coshepherd - Grid Engine single job-controlling agent

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ssggee__ccoosshheepphheerrdd

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _s_g_e___c_o_s_h_e_p_h_e_r_d  is  needed to run the token manipulation executables if
       Grid Engine is run in an AFS environment.  It is started by  the  shep-
       herd process and belongs to the same PAG (process authentication group)
       as the shepherd and the user's job, babysitting AFS tokens as specified
       by sseett__ttookkeenn__ccmmdd and ttookkeenn__eexxtteenndd__ttiimmee of _s_g_e___c_o_n_f(5).

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _s_g_e___s_h_e_p_h_e_r_d(5), _s_g_e___c_o_n_f(1).

CCOOPPYYRRIIGGHHTT
       See _s_g_e___i_n_t_r_o(1) for a full statement of rights and permissions.



